<a name="Question Statistics">
<h4>
2.5.2. Question Statistics
</h4>
</a>
<p>
When the user selects <tt>Statistics</tt> in the <tt>Menu</tt> tab and the <tt>Question</tt> tab, the system
displays the dialog shown in Figure 2.5.2.

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Question Statistic dialog">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/question-stats.jpg" height="400" width="350">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2.5.2:  Question Statistic dialog.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
</br>
<p>A question will be reprensented in the form of a row.</p>
<ul>
   <li>The <tt>Checkbox</tt> column will allow the user to select one test.
   <li>The <tt>Question Name</tt> column is the name of the question in the question bank.
   <li>The <tt>Difficulty</tt> column is the difficulty level of the question
   <li>The <tt>Last Used</tt> column is the date when the question was used last.

</ul>
<p>The <tt>View Statistics</tt> button will create a graph for the selected question that is shown in the bottom half of the dialog</br>
The <tt>Edit Question</tt> button will allow the user to bring up a dialog to edit the quesiton. This scenario is described in <a href="edit-ques.html">Section 2.2.1</a></p>
